reviews.text: This Japanese restaurant is hidden in a quiet basement corner of K11 Mall. It must be one of very few restaurants in TST where you can dine comfortably with ample space between each table, especially considering its inexpensive price. Although the food isn't top notch most of the modern Japanese dishes are tasty.
Pretty good izakaya place w good spacious seating
Sushi is not good. But the atmosphere is very nice. Suitable for friends meeting.

Apart from the vip room we were the only customers, service was ok, but there’s no vibe.  Food standard was at least a notch down from the standard at Times Square branch.  Sad to see a favourite going down hill...
Sushi is not appetising due to freshness,  there was a mosquito in miso soup. One time visit only
